Being a Chinese citizen changes everything. You have a massive home-field advantage: you don't need a WFOE, a JV, or foreign visas. You can legally own the ICP license and run the Mini Program as an individual (with limits) or as a domestic company (recommended). [1, 2] 
Here is your streamlined "Native" Startup Plan for 2026:
## Phase 1: The "Individual" Lean Launch (Fastest Route)
As a Chinese citizen with a National ID (身份证), you can launch a personal WeChat Mini-Program immediately.

* The Cost: Almost ¥0.
* The Limit: Personal Mini-Programs cannot include user-generated content (forums/gossip), payment features, or commercial buttons.
* The Strategy: Build a read-only "Salary Tool" first.
* Feature: "Search 2026 Tech Salaries."
   * Data: Manually curate verified data from verified sources (like Maimai screenshots or friends in HR).
   * Why: This builds your user base without triggering the strict "community" license requirements.

## Phase 2: The "Domestic Company" Upgrade (Real Business)
To add the "Gossip/Anonymous" features and make money, you eventually need a business license. But for you, this is simple. [3] 

* Registration: Register a domestic company (e.g., a "Tech Consulting" LTD).
* Cost: ~¥0-500 RMB (many cities offer free registration for local entrepreneurs).
   * Speed: 3-7 days. [4] 
* The "Community" License:
* Once you have the business license, apply for the "Non-Commercial ICP Filing" (ICP Beian).
   * Crucial Upgrade: Apply for the "Community/Forum" category in the WeChat Mini-Program backend. Note: This is still strict. You may need to show you have a content moderation team. [5] 

## Phase 3: Tech & Compliance (The Native Stack)
Don't use Western tech. Use the standard domestic stack to save money and avoid blocks.

* Hosting: Tencent Cloud (腾讯云) or Aliyun (阿里云).
* Pro Tip: Use WeChat Cloud Development (云开发). It effectively gives you a free backend/database for small Mini-Programs and requires zero server maintenance.
* Identity: Use WeChat Login. It automatically handles the "Real-Name" requirement because every WeChat user is already verified with their bank/ID. You don't need to build your own SMS system initially.
* Moderation (Critical): Connect to Aliyun Green (内容安全) or Tencent Cloud AMS.
* Why: It costs pennies per check and automatically filters political/illegal keywords so you don't get shut down by the police.

## Growth Strategy: The "Private Domain" (私域流量)
Since you can't buy ads on Google/Facebook:

   1. WeChat Groups: Create invite-only groups for "P7/P8 Alibaba Employees" or "ByteDance Commercial Team." Seed your Mini-Program there.
   2. Xiaohongshu (Little Red Book): Post salary comparisons as images. Put your Mini-Program name in the comments. Do not put links; they will be blocked. [6] 

## Summary Checklist

| Step [6] | Action | Cost (RMB) | Time |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Register Personal Mini-Program | ¥0 | 1 Day |
| 2 | Build "Salary Search" MVP | ¥0 (Self-code) | 2 Weeks |
| 3 | Register Domestic Company | ~¥500 | 1 Week |
| 4 | Upgrade to Enterprise Account | ¥300 / year | 3 Days |
| 5 | Launch "Gossip" Features | (Dev Cost) | Month 2 |

One question to decide your start: Do you know how to code (specifically Vue.js or React)? If yes, you can build the Mini-Program yourself using Uni-app or Taro (cross-platform frameworks popular in China). If not, you will need a technical co-founder.

